Fortnite Code-Along

HtmlCssReview/HtmlCssReviewCodeAlong.htm.title: Fortnite Code-Along
HtmlCssReview/HtmlCssReviewCodeAlong.htm.body:
HTML & CSS Review Code-Along
Start by forking this empty Repl, then follow the instructions below to build a simple webpage!
To fork the Repl, click the "Fork Repl" button on the page:

Add the Basic HTML Elements
Add the foundational elements to the index.html file. Start with , then add  and  between the html tags.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ


    
    
    
    


Add a Main Header
Between the opening and closing body tags, add an h3 element. Within the h3 element, add the proper text.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

Fortnite Fan Site

Add an Image
Add an image to the page.

Go to Google Images
Find an image, and copy the image address/URL/location
Create an img element, and set its src attribute to be the URL for the image



üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ



Add a Paragraph about Fortnite
Under the img element, add a p element that contains the text for the paragraph. Talk about your favorite game: Fortnite.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ


    Fortnite is a great video game filled with several memorable characters and lots of action.


Add Another Header
Under the p, add an h3 header... and inside, put My Favorite Character.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

My Favorite Character

Add a Paragraph about Your Favorite Character
Under the h3, create a p element. Between the opening and closing tags, describe your favorite Fortnite character.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ


    My fave Fortnite character is definitely Drift! He's so cool with his rad moves and sick outfits. I love getting all the skins for him.


Add a Background Style
Now it's time to add some style. Between the opening and closing head tags, add a style element.
Add a ruleset to the style element that will select the body (all the content on the page). Within the ruleset, set the background property to black, and the color property to white.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ


    body {
        background: black;
        color: white;
    }


Add an Image Style
Currently, the image might be a little big. Use CSS to update its size. Add another ruleset to the style element that will select the img. Within the ruleset, set the height property to 200px.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

img {
    height: 200px;
}

Add a Main Header Style
Next, it would be nice for the main header to stand out a little more. To style only the main header, add a class attribute to it in the HTML, and then select it by its class in the CSS.
In the index.html file, find the top h3 header. Add a class attribute with a value of shiny to the element.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

Fortnite Fan Site

In the style element, add a ruleset that will select elements with a class of shiny using .shiny. Within the ruleset, set the color property to gold so that everyone knows you are legendary.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

.shiny {
    color: gold;
}

Final Code
That's it! The Fortnite Fan Site looks pretty good.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ


    
        
            body {
                background: black;
                color: white;
            }
            img {
                height: 200px;
            }
            .shiny {
                color: gold;
            }
        
    
    
        Fortnite Fan Site
        
        
            Fortnite is a great video game filled with several memorable characters and lots of action.
        
        My Favorite Character
        
            My fave Fortnite character is definitely Drift! He's so cool with his rad moves and sick outfits. I love getting all the skins for him.

IntroToJS/StudentDesc.html.body:
Introduction to JavaScript
Today's lesson is all about getting familiar with this powerful programming language! You'll learn how to add JavaScript to your HTML pages and start exploring the ways it can make your website interactive.
"If HTML is the body and CSS is the clothes, JavaScript is the mind."
-- Unknown
Introduction to JavaScript Presentation


JavaScript Variables Presentation


Code-Along Activity: Basic Chatbot
Click here for the code-along instructions.
Self-Paced Exercise: Make it Chatty
Use what you learned today to "upgrade" your chatbot. Have it ask the user even more personal questions!

IntroToJS/IntroToJSCodeAlong.html.title: Chatbot Code-Along
IntroToJS/IntroToJSCodeAlong.html.body:
Basic Chatbot Code-Along
For this exercise, start by forking this empty Repl.

Then, follow along with the instructor to build a little text-based JavaScript program. The program will prompt the user with a question and will then reply back with an alert message containing the user's answer.
Create the JavaScript File
In the Files section on the left, click the New file button. Give the new file a name of script.js.
Within the script.js file, add a statement that will show a welcome message to the user.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

alert("Welcome to the chatbot!");

Link the JavaScript File

In the index.html, add a  element
Within the  element, add a  element
Add a src attribute to the  opening tag to point to the script.js file



üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ


    
        
    


Run the webpage, and make sure the alert() pop-up with the message appears!

Note: a  is not required for this HTML page.

Ask a Question
Ask the user for their name and show a text box to the user allowing them to type their answer. Be sure to choose a descriptive variable name to store this value!


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

let username = prompt("What's your name?");

Display a Reply
Show the user a formatted message containing their name.


üëÄ Click to Reveal Code üëÄ

alert("Cool! I love the name '" + username + "'. I think it means 'smart.'");
